  <summary>1/8/1987--Introduced.
Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to extend coverage to include expenses incurred in providing a Papanicolaou test or a mammogram for the diagnosis of uterine or breast cancer, if the individual receiving the test has not had such a test on a routine basis during the preceding six months.</summary>
